# Styling Rules

## Tailwind CSS v4

This project uses Tailwind CSS v4 with the new CSS-first configuration. Theme variables are defined in `src/app/globals.css`.

## Color Palette

### Dark Mode (Default)
- Background: `bg-neutral-950` (near black)
- Card background: `bg-neutral-900/50` (translucent dark)
- Borders: `border-neutral-800`
- Primary text: `text-neutral-50` (white)
- Secondary text: `text-neutral-400`
- Muted text: `text-neutral-500`
- Accent/Primary: `text-red-400`, `bg-red-500`

### CSS Variables
```css
--primary: oklch(0.637 0.237 25.331);  /* Red accent */
--background: oklch(0.12 0.01 285);     /* Near black */
--card: oklch(0.17 0.015 285);          /* Slightly lighter */
--muted-foreground: oklch(0.65 0.02 285); /* Gray text */
```

## Common Patterns

### Page Container
```tsx
<div className="space-y-6 pb-20">
  {/* pb-20 for mobile bottom nav clearance */}
</div>
```

### Cards
```tsx
// Standard card
<Card className="border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/50">

// Highlighted/active card
<Card className="border-red-500/30 bg-red-500/5">

// Dashed border (for empty states)
<Card className="border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900/30 border-dashed">
```

### Buttons
```tsx
// Primary (red bg, dark text)
<Button>Primary Action</Button>

// Outline
<Button variant="outline">Secondary</Button>

// Ghost
<Button variant="ghost" size="icon">
  <Icon className="w-4 h-4" />
</Button>

// Destructive styling on outline
<Button variant="outline" className="border-red-500/50 text-red-400 hover:bg-red-500/10">
```

### Inputs
```tsx
<Input className="bg-neutral-800 border-neutral-700" />
<Input className="bg-neutral-800/50 border-neutral-700" /> // More transparent
```

### Text Hierarchy
```tsx
<h1 className="text-2xl font-bold">Page Title</h1>
<p className="text-neutral-400 mt-1">Subtitle</p>

<h2 className="text-lg font-semibold">Section Title</h2>

<span className="text-sm text-neutral-500">Meta text</span>
```

### Spacing
- Use `space-y-*` for vertical stacking
- Use `gap-*` in flex/grid layouts
- Common values: `space-y-2`, `space-y-4`, `space-y-6`, `gap-2`, `gap-3`, `gap-4`

### Gradients
```tsx
// Background gradient
<div className="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-950 via-neutral-900 to-neutral-950">

// Red glow overlay
<div className="bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_top,_var(--tw-gradient-stops))] from-red-950/20 via-transparent to-transparent">
```

### Icons
Always use lucide-react icons:
```tsx
import { Loader2, Plus, Check, ChevronRight } from "lucide-react";

<Loader2 className="w-4 h-4 animate-spin" />
<Plus className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
```

### Responsive
- Mobile-first approach
- Use `md:` prefix for desktop styles
- Bottom nav is `md:hidden`, top nav is `hidden md:flex`

### Animations
```tsx
// Spinner
<Loader2 className="animate-spin" />

// Pulse (for live indicators)
<div className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-red-500 animate-pulse" />

// Backdrop blur
<div className="backdrop-blur-lg bg-neutral-950/80">
```
